stylometry:
Transportation is when something is transported from the direct origin to its destination. Something is taken from the factory directly to the store. It deals more with the transportation of the items from the origin to the destination to sell. 

Transshipment is when things can be taken from warehouses to stores, or shippped between warehouses or stores. The best example is the problem I had for homework about all of the cars being shipped in between dealerships, warehouses, and manufacturers. Cars were being shipped from two manufacturers to 4 dealerships and two warehouses around the country, at the same time the warehouses were shipping cars to the dealerships to get rid of inventory. 

Node: the destinations (warehouses, dealerships, manufacture)
Arcs: the transportation to each destination (transportation costs to each destination)
Flows: the item or inventory being shipped (cars)
